 BR quest 'cept for Clockwork Stout, BB Swig and Blood Spirits. How did all you under-30 people get the Blood Spirits? I've been wanting to get a group in MM and get them, but I've heard that the castle is too much for a group my lv. Ive been 25 for 2 weeks now, frankly because I'm bloody tired of fighting Sarnaks. Letting someone else kill them and me loot them is not a real viable option, since no one on Morell Thule ever goes to MM, and my guild is all the same lv as me. So what should I do? Is the castle as hard as people say, or is it lack of pulling skills that turns that place into Grand Central Station so frequently? If I do get a group to go there, what classes/lvs should I get for the group? Thanks in advance for the input, guys. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=janelane>JaneLane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/6/01 3:40:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How'd you guys get the Blood Spirts?</span><hr size=1> I got my bloodspirits by &quot;cherry picking&quot; them from a lvl 50+ ranger and 50+ cleric that were heading into MM to camp the hooded black cloak, which is in a room just beyond the cY where the bloodspirits drop.<br>
<br>
The fact that a nice item drops near the CY should create a steady flow of people heading there to camp the cloak.  My recommendation it to head to MM on a Friday or Saturday night when everyone in the friggin world is online and piggyback with another group to get it.<br>
<br>
Basically a group of 20-somethings will get creamed trying to fight their way in.<br>
<br>
If you are dead determined to earn it, the only way I could see a lower lvl group pulling it off is to head into the fountain room invised.  Once in, clear the room (3 mobs).  Then pull mobs from the CY to the fountain room.  I know that in the 40s this strategy will pull no more than 2 or 3 mobs at a time.  I can't say for sure if a lvl 25 tries it that he won't pull the whole friggin CY.  Heh, one way to find out.<br>
<br>
In the fountain room nothing from the CY will aggro except the one roamer that goes right to the threshold to the room.  As long as you don't let any mobs get outside the fountain room (i.e. make damn sure you snare or root the last mob) you have a chance to pull it off.<br>
<br>
Good luck, I hope you enjoy the quest. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upatofnaud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>patofnaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/01 12:00:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How'd you guys get the Blood Spirts?</span><hr size=1> Mistmoore is nickname Trainmoore for a reason. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You group can easily handle any of the mobs on the way to the Garden individually, but Mayong Mistomoore will have none of that. <br>
<br>
Once you get past the Graveyard, it seams every mob you aggro will bring two friends, and they bring two friends each, then send psychic message to thier friends in the Castle, then the next thing you see is a SEA of blue heading your way.<br>
<br>
Even at 52, no way could I solo my way in past that much green.<br>
<br>
I am on Morell-Thule, I did get mine by /ooc'ing if anyone was &quot;camping the HBC&quot; and snuck up to loot mine. Thanks to Sojurn and Pynkis. If I am not busy some night and have a few friends with me I can do the same for you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uyalum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yalum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/01 1:12:20 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How'd you guys get the Blood Spirts?</span><hr size=1> Heh, Sojurn and Pynkis both retired ages ago... I got mine by asking the ~10 people camping butler/maid if they'd mind if I looted the hemo whenever they got around to pulling it.  They said sure and immediately pulled it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
And I've got a clockwork oil stout in the bank, and no clue what to do with it.  It's yours if you want it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/hottopic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/01 3:00:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How'd you guys get the Blood Spirts?</span><hr size=1> Very similar - I was 25 and did the /ooc.  Cinte (yes, I still remember) told me to come on up... if I dared <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Well, skulking through MM is fantastic.  But I was still young and skulking through a sea of red mobs left me sweating.  I got to the room and I put to use my '<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://how.to/stayhidden">loot while hiding</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->' techniques to try to avoid getting agro'd.<br>
<br>
The next day, I found a group in SolA and they were willing to add me to the group long enough to contribute to the Laryssa fight.  Later that night, redemption! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubladesake.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bladesake</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/01 9:24:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How'd you guys get the Blood Spirts?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the replys. Ill get with some of you in game (I assume that your character names are your posting names) sometime since your willing to help. I could use all that I can get. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3236.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=3230.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3222.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3222.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3222.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicI